  "chapter": {
    "number": 38,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Hezekiah’s Illness and Recovery"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "In those days Hezekiah became mortally ill. The prophet Isaiah son of Amoz came to him and said, “This is what the LORD says: ‘Put your house in order, for you are about to die; you will not recover.’”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "Then Hezekiah turned his face to the wall and prayed to the LORD,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "saying, “Please, O LORD, remember how I have walked before You faithfully and with wholehearted devotion; I have done what was good in Your sight.” And Hezekiah wept bitterly."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "And the word of the LORD came to Isaiah, saying,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "“Go and tell Hezekiah that this is what the LORD, the God of your father David, says: ‘I have heard your prayer; I have seen your tears. Behold, I will add fifteen years to your life."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "And I will deliver you and this city from the hand of the king of Assyria. I will defend this city.",
          {
            "noteId": 2641
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "This will be a sign to you from the LORD that He will do what He has promised:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "I will make the sun’s shadow that falls on the stairway of Ahaz go back ten steps.’”",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "So the sunlight went back the ten steps it had descended."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Hezekiah’s Song of Thanksgiving"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "This is a writing by Hezekiah king of Judah after his illness and recovery:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I said, “In the prime",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2642
          },
          {
            "text": "of my life",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I must go through the gates of Sheol",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and be deprived of the remainder of my years.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I said, “I will never again see the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even the LORD, in the land of the living;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will no longer look on mankind",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with those who dwell in this world.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My dwelling has been picked up and removed from me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a shepherd’s tent.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I have rolled up my life like a weaver;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He cuts me off from the loom;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "from day until night You make an end of me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I composed myself",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2643
          },
          {
            "text": "until the morning.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Like a lion He breaks all my bones;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "from day until night You make an end of me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I chirp like a swallow or crane;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I moan like a dove.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "My eyes grow weak as I look upward.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O Lord, I am oppressed; be my security.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What can I say?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has spoken to me, and He Himself has done this.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will walk slowly all my years",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because of the anguish of my soul.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O Lord, by such things men live,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and in all of them my spirit finds life.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You have restored me to health",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and have let me live.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely for my own welfare",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I had such great anguish;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but Your love has delivered me from the pit of oblivion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for You have cast all my sins behind Your back.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For Sheol cannot thank You;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Death cannot praise You.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Those who descend to the Pit",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "cannot hope for Your faithfulness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The living, only the living, can thank You,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as I do today;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "fathers will tell their children",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "about Your faithfulness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD will save me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we will play songs on stringed instruments",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "all the days of our lives",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the house of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "Now Isaiah had said, “Prepare a lump of pressed figs and apply it to the boil, and he will recover.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "And Hezekiah had asked, “What will be the sign that I will go up to the house of the LORD?”"
        ]
      }
    ],
